MonitoringLocationName: Big Sandy Creek 20m Upstream of FM 1276 Bridge
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: This stream, which changes its name to Village Creek downstream of this point, is sampled at its crossing under the FM 1276 bridge, at the downstream end of the Big Sandy Creek Unit.  This site represents a headwater site within the Village Creek watershed. Two additional sites will be sampled, at approximate mid and end-points of Village Creek. Upstream of the Big Sandy Creek is the Alabama-Coushatta Indian Reservation (location of a TCEQ Clean Rivers sampling site).

OrganizationFormalName: National Park Service Water Resources Division
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: The station is located on the Rocky Creek, TexasBlanco County 7.5 minute (topographic) quadrangle. The site is located at the Pedernales River near the Farm Road 1320 Bridge.  Data at this station have been collected by the Lower Colorado River Authority (LCRA) since 1984.  Historically, LCRA provided their data to the Texas Natural Resource Conservation Commission (TNRCC) and the TNRCC uploaded some of the data for this site to EPA Legacy STORET under Organization ID 21TXWQB at STORET Station ID 12375.  These data uploaded by the TNRCC are presently available for public retrieval at EPA's STORET Legacy Data Center.  The data entered into STORET by the National Park Service at its version of the same site, STORET Station ID LYJO_LCRA_1320, contains only those LCRA water and sediment records not uploaded to Legacy STORET by the TNRCC.  For more information about LCRA, contact Jerry Guajardo at the LCRA; P.O. Box 220; Austin, TX 78767; (tel. 5124733200).

For more information about LCRA, contact Jerry Guajardo at the LCRA; P.O. Box 220; Austin, TX 78767; (tel. 5124733200).
